headline: Is It Too Late To Consider AIG After Strong Five Year Share Price Performance?
summary: If you are wondering whether American International Group at around $76 a share is still worth buying, or if the easy gains are behind it, you are not alone. That is exactly what this breakdown is here to unpack. The stock is roughly flat in the short term, down 0.4% over the last week and 0.8% over the past month, but it is still up 4.6% year to date and 5.2% over the last year, with a 123.0% return over five years pointing to a longer term rerating story. headline: Assessing AIG’s Valuation as Its Turnaround Progresses and Investor Optimism Builds
summary: American International Group (AIG) has been quietly reshaping its business, and recent trading hints at investors reassessing what they are willing to pay for the insurer’s improving earnings and cash generation. headline: 1 Large-Cap Stock on Our Buy List and 2 We Turn Down
summary: Large-cap stocks have the power to shape entire industries thanks to their size and widespread influence. With such vast footprints, however, finding new areas for growth is much harder than for smaller, more agile players.
